		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>My favorite way of cooking hard-boiled eggs is in the oven. Alton Brown recommends this, and it allows you to cook a lot of them in a more &#8216;gentle&#8217; fashion outside of turbulent boiling water. You still dunk them in cold water upon completion, so this trick would still work.</p>
<p>Alton recommends placing the eggs on the oven rack itself. (with aluminum foil on the bottom of the oven just in case something breaks)</p>
<p>325 degrees for 30 minutes.</p>
