		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>Sheez. That&#8217;s not how you cook boiled eggs. That is way overcooking, you Viking! </p>
<p>Bring the eggs and water to boiling and then take the pan off the heat and let it sit for 20 minutes. You will get perfectly boiled eggs! Seriously. Who cares about putting all that energy into peeling an over-cooked egg?</p>
<p>Try it you&#8217;ll like it. Maybe the baking soda and your method will work with this type of egg too.</p>
