<li class=" comment" id="comment-23128">
	<div id="div-comment-23128">
		<div class="comment_meta">
			<span class="comment_author">Ryan</span>
			<br />
			<span class="comment_time">
				July 3rd, 2008				<br />
				<a href="#comment-23128" alt="Permalink to this comment">10:31 pm</a>
			</span>
			<br />
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/72e657cc8585113c45090311fbd5bbcb?s=64&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-64 photo' height='64' width='64' />		</div>
		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>Pretty cool, though I think this is even easier:</p>
<p>(not sure if it matters how the egg is boiled, but since I never boil eggs myself, it&#8217;s always worked with any that have been presented to me)</p>
<p>Palm a hard boiled egg, hold it 6-12 inches above a hard surface, and then smack it down. Keep your hand on the egg, and while applying a medium amount of pressure, roll your hand over the top so that the egg does one complete revolution (the shell will be cracking while you do this).</p>
<p>Now, simply use both hands and try to pry the shell off from the middle into two pieces&#8230;it will usually come off in one piece (held together by the membrane inside).</p>
<p>I only eat them once every few months, but it&#8217;s easy enough to pick up right where you left off &#8211; impressing skeptical friends! If you&#8217;re good, you can do this in about 5 seconds.</p>
					</div>
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/blog/2008/07/02/how-to-peel-hard-boiled-eggs-without-peeling/?replytocom=23128#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-23128", "23128", "respond", "378")'>Reply</a>	</div>
