<li class=" comment" id="comment-66232">
	<div id="div-comment-66232">
		<div class="comment_meta">
			<span class="comment_author">Sarah</span>
			<br />
			<span class="comment_time">
				May 17th, 2010				<br />
				<a href="#comment-66232" alt="Permalink to this comment">10:57 pm</a>
			</span>
			<br />
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c16b944b46e6bacd9e00659f92248605?s=64&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-64 photo' height='64' width='64' />		</div>
		<div class="comment_entry">
			<p>8 Minute Cake:<br />
My friend, Cassie, just posted this on Facebook. Definitely so much quicker!</p>
<p>NEEDS:<br />
Cake Mix (any flavor)<br />
Tub of frosting (that compliments your cake)<br />
Oil<br />
Eggs<br />
Water<br />
Lg. microwave safe plastic bowl<br />
Large cookie sheet (with a brim- think sheet cake pan.)</p>
<p>Step 1: make the cake according to the directions on the back of the box. Mix in the plastic bowl.<br />
Step 2: Empty the container of frosting directly into the middle of the cake batter</p>
<p>Step 3: Put it in the microwave for 8 minutes.<br />
Step 4: Behold the glory of what comes out of the microwave&#8230;.Mmmmm! Let it sit for about 2 mins.</p>
<p>Step 4: Place the cookie sheet on top of the bowl and invert.<br />
(that means flip over)<br />
Step 5: Lift bowl. Careful- steam is HOT.</p>
<p>Step 6: Marvel at the awesomeness, smell the incredible aroma, shove other guests out of the way and move in with intent to eat and destroy- fork in hand.<br />
She says &#8220;Our favorite flavor combination is Devils food cake with Cream Cheese Frosting. Others have raved about the Lemon cake with Vanilla. It&#8217;s your cake. Party on.&#8221;</p>
					</div>
